Title: Missile Warning / Missile Tracking - MEO Epoch 2                                                                                       -     307.440        485.647
Description: This activity funds development of Medium Earth Orbit Epoch 2 space vehicles, up to four launches planned to
deliver up to four planes of capability (12-24 space vehicles) by FY 2030 and supporting ground efforts with operations necessary
to deliver Initial Warfighting Capability for Medium Earth Orbit architecture. Medium Earth Orbit Epoch 2 builds upon Medium
Earth Orbit Epoch 1 to meet Capability Development Document requirements through agile development. The Medium Earth
Orbit Epoch 2 acquisition will balance delivery of the Initial Warfighting Capability while establishing a path toward delivering
Fully Warfighting Capability in future epochs. The Medium Earth Orbit Epoch 2 prototyping effort will deliver a new global tracking
access mission capability to contain raids of advanced hypersonic and ballistic missiles. This effort will demonstrate the ability to
function within a coordinated Overhead Persistent Infrared enterprise, which receives taskings from the Joint Overhead Persistent
Infrared Planning Center, executes that tasking through sensor collections and delivers missile data back to the enterprise. All
space vehicles will operate in an integrated fashion through a common ground system rooted in the Future Operationally Resilient
Ground Evolution (FORGE) framework. Medium Earth Orbit Epoch 2 space vehicle design, build, integration and test efforts
began in FY 2025. This effort also funds mission data processing, command and control, ground operations, ground entry points

