FY 2025 Plans:
FY2025 plans under E1 Major Thrust
FY 2026 Plans:
Space: Continue Epoch 2 activities to include managing multiple contracts executing space system development, ground
segment development, and integration at our operating center. Will consist of preliminary and critical design reviews that finalize
the designs. Primes will transition from design to build of space vehicles and ground development. Epoch 2 will build out the
architecture for global missile tracking with up to four planes of additional capability.

Ground: Begin site surveys and selection process for additional Ground Entry Point (GEP) locations needed for Epoch 2. Initiate
and award Ground Management and Integration contract to add Epoch 2 capability to the Medium Earth Orbit Space Operations
Center (MSOC), to build a Backup MSOC, and to build additional GEPs. Start design of Epoch 2 MSOC fit up for additional space
vehicle provider operations at Boulder Ground Innovation Facility, design of Backup MSOC, & additional GEPs.

Funds allow both space and ground efforts to rapidly respond to implement system resiliency and situational awareness
necessary to operate in the contested space domain. Activities may include, but are not limited to program office support, studies,
technical analysis, experimentation, risk reduction, prototyping, and activities that may leverage commercial, U.S. Government
partnership, and international opportunities to respond to existing and emerging adversarial threats with speed and agility.
FY 2025 to FY 2026 Increase/Decrease Statement:
FY 2026 increase due to continuing execution of MEO Epoch 2 spacecraft and constellation design, build, test, and associated
ground activities.
