                                                                                 Accomplishments/Planned Programs Subtotals                  3.435      18.503          23.763$$, $$$$, $$The strategy to develop, integrate, and test Improved Vehicle Safety Technologies is to leverage active safety capabilities developed commercially and adapt for military
use on the FMTV. The development and integration will be conducted via STS Task Order with the vehicle OEM.

 The Army partnered with Operational Energy-Innovation (OE-I) and Defense Innovation Unit (DIU) to fund an Other Transaction Agreement (OTA) for rapid prototype
 design and test of Vehicle Export Power such as Vehicle Integrated Power Kits (VIPK) to conclude 2QFY28. The Army is targeting 4QFY28 to award an ECP cut-in to
 production line.

 The strategy supports the development, integration, and testing of an All-Season Arctic (Winter) tire for the Family of Medium Tactical Vehicles (FMTV) to enhance the
 operational capability and safety of these vehicles in cold-weather environments, particularly on snow and ice. The tires will be provisioned for the A1P2 and A2 vehicles
 and units will order them directly. The Army will conduct test via a MIPR to NATC.

