A. Mission Description and Budget Item Justification
This project supports continued modernization of the Army's Family of Medium Tactical Wheeled Vehicle (FMTV) fleet: 4x4 and 6x6 Cargo, Tractor, Load Handling
System (LHS), Wrecker, Expandable Van, Shop Van, and Dump Truck variants with payloads ranging from 2.5-tons to 10-tons and associated companion trailers.
Modernization includes upgrades in survivability, safety, modularity, fuel efficiency, power generation, reliability, maintainability, mobility, autonomous operation, and
other emerging technologies that enhance warfighter capability. The Family of Medium Tactical Wheeled Vehicles perform the majority of the Army's local haul, line haul,
and unit resupply missions throughout theater as multi-purpose transportation vehicles in combat, combat support, and combat service support units. The FMTV also
serves as a host platform for Long Range Precision Fires (LRPF), Air and Missile Defense (AMD), and Counter - Unmanned Aerial Systems (C-UAS) supporting Fire
Control and Communication modules, and other support areas for maintenance/personnel.

 This project supports development and integration of export power capability for AMD units: PM THAAD (Terminal High Altitude Area Defense), Patriot Missile System,
 Sentinel Integrated Fire Protection Capability (IFPC), and Integrated Battle Command System (IBCS)/Integrated Fire Control Network (IFCN). The Vehicle Integrated
 Power Kit (VIPK) will provide 20kW on the move and up to 120 kW of exportable power from the vehicle that will be utilized for command and control, directed energy
 weapons, radar systems, and missile launchers.

 FY 2027 funds in the amount of $3.763 million will be used for continued development and integration of Improved Vehicle Safety Technologies, including active safety
 technologies such as front collision warning, collision mitigation, lane keeping assist, adaptive cruise control, and 360-degree situational awareness.

 FY 2027 funds in the amount of $5.000 million will fund development of a winter rated tire for the FMTV that improves safety and mobility in cold weather environments.

 FY 2027 funds in the amount of $15.000 million will be used for development and integration of Vehicle Export Power such as, Vehicle Integrated Power Kits (VIPK) that
 provide exportable power generated by FMTV platforms to improve mobility and agility for rapid emplacement/displacement of dismount operations and fire support.

