Note
This program, BA 6, PE 1206399SF, project 664111, Space Futures, is a new start.

 FY 2026: a total of 110.598M was realigned and consolidated from multiple Space Systems Command (SSC) PEs into this new PE 1206399SF for increased
 transparency and efficient execution of basic operating costs for Space Systems Integration Office (SSIO) enterprise engineering support. It is not a New Start.

A. Mission Description and Budget Item Justification
In 2021, the Space Force stood up Space Systems Command (SSC), including establishing the SSIO. In July 2024, the Assistant Secretary of the Air Force for Space
Acquisition and Integration (ASAF) broadened SSIO's mission and designated SSIO as the responsible organization for integration across all Space Force Program
Executive Officer (PEO) portfolios to include SSC, Space Development Agency (SDA), and the Space Rapid Capabilities Office (SpRCO). In April 2025, the ASAF also
appointed the Senior Advisor to the Service Acquisition Executive, and in response to a 2025 NDAA requirement, the Senior Advisor for Space Command, Control, and
Integration (SASC2I). The SASAE is the USSF lead for space enterprise system-of-systems engineering across the space acquisition enterprise and is responsible to
drive engineering and assess all acquisition efforts under the authority of the ASAF portfolio and applicable mission partner organizations, to include the advisement
of the SAE on matters of enforcement needed to enable and drive integrated enterprise capability delivery. The SASC2I is responsible for conducting oversight of all
acquisition efforts within the authority of the ASAF with respect to developing, upgrading, deploying, and sustaining space command, control, and integration to meet the
space command, control, and integration requirements of the combatant commands. SSIO conducts systems engineering analysis and integration for space programs
and vastly increases collaboration across the entire USSF space enterprise to deliver fully integrated space warfighting capability.

 SSIO orchestrates end-to-end capability delivery and warfighter operations across all Space Force PEOs, Space Force Field Commands, Combatant Commands, and
 mission partners such as Department of the Air Force Rapid Capabilities Office (DAFRCO), the Missile Defense Agency (MDA), and the National Reconnaissance
 Office (NRO), and advises the ASAF on strategy to optimize PEO portfolios across all mission areas to meet warfighting needs. These efforts also provide systems
 engineering for the space component of the Command Control Communications and Battle Management (C3BM) program to deliver an integrated Command and
 Control architecture to support the joint fight. SSIO enterprise-level integration includes three lines of effort. The first is Enterprise Mission Integration and Analysis
 which supports a multitude of Space Force programs at all classification levels needed to close mission threads and kill chains across the USSF and deliver a cohesive
 warfighting technical baseline for the Nation. The second is Enterprise Technical Governance and Requirements management. The third is Space Futures which will
 define the future operating environment, prioritize science and technology initiatives, and wargaming required to refine operational concepts.



