FY 2025 Plans:
Completes the multi-year development/delivery of seven mid-to-large aperture fixed collection and associated
processing capabilities for the 73 ISR Squadron at OCONUS and CONUS sites. Begins refurbishment of final,
large aperture in support of INDO-PACOM requirements; digitizes ISR processing architecture to increase
collection capacity and data veracity. Begins three-year effort to modernize eight mid-sized apertures at
OCONUS and CONUS locations; modernizes digital architecture to allow for "Sun Synchronous" operational
control automation across multiple AORs for efficient collection and processing architecture. Continues
installation, assessments and Authority to Operate (ATO) of mission management planning enhancements
and robust collection automation capability, compliant with Risk Management Framework (RMF) requirements.
Begins refurbishment of large, multi-band antenna array. Continues development of Space Intelligence
deployable capabilities, including small form factor solutions for 72 ISRS, Peterson SFB, CO in support of

