discoverable, and upgrades to a GEOINT ISR exploitation tool suite, in support of CCMDs and the IC.
FY 2026 Base Plans:
Continues refurbishment of final, large aperture in support of INDO-PACOM requirements; further enhances
automated intelligence processing architecture to increase collection capacity and data veracity. Continues
further prototype development of contractor "fly-off” winner for best available enhancement of fixed/mobile
ISR Processing, Exploitation and Dissemination (PED) capabilities via latest hardware/software technology,
digital processing, automation and supportable with high speed connectivity. Begin full development of
fully operational Space Intelligence deployable capabilities, including small form factor solutions for 72
ISRS, Peterson SFB, CO in support of Continental United States (CONUS)-based deployable Tactical ISR
Operations Cells (TISROCs)/Deployable ISR Support Cells (DISCs) to meet USSF Service-retained and
CCMD intelligence collection requirements. Begins full recapitalization of fixed processing systems to current
Intelligence Community hardware/software baseline. Continues second year of three-year effort to modernize
eight mid-sized apertures at OCONUS and CONUS locations; continues modernization of digital architecture
to allow for "Sun Synchronous" operational control automation across multiple AORs for efficient collection and
processing architecture. Completes refurbishment of large, multi-band antenna array. Continues installation,
assessments and Authority to Operate (ATO) of mission management planning enhancements and robust
collection automation capability to fulfill Risk Management Framework (RMF) requirements. Instantiates a Radio
Frequency search and survey tool enhancement. Continues enhancements to data dissemination capabilities.
Continues funding for support to exploitation, vulnerability and susceptibility analysis. Investments in multi-
INT Space Intelligence Production Cell (SIPC) fused intelligence completed. Continues funding for updates to
analytic exploitation, vulnerability and susceptibility analysis, contributing to development of operational tactics,

