       Change Summary Explanation
       FY 2024: Decrease of 6.00 million due to below threshold requirement, to support other Space Force priorities.
       FY 2025: Net decrease of 111.284 million, decrease of 89.031 million due to congressional directed transfer to Space Rapid Capabilities Office, PE 1206857SF
       and decrease of 22.253 million due to congressional directed reduction for acquisition strategy change.
       FY 2026: Decrease of 107.652 million due to transfer to Rapid Resilient Command and Control, PE 1206772SF to consolidate functions for efficiency and
       improve transparency.

C. Accomplishments/Planned Programs ($ in Millions)                                                                                FY 2024     FY 2025      FY 2026
Title: Rapid Resilient Command and Control (R2C2) Development                                                                        104.853       0.000        0.000
Description: Develop and integrate common satellite operations ground segment solution (SatOps) command and control
(C2) services in cloud environments. Refine standards and interfaces, develop and implement cybersecurity and cryptography
requirements, develop training, address Zero Trust, mature antenna network services and connectivity, and integrate capabilities
into the enterprise. Support mission partner demonstrations, integration, and test of mission-unique software.

FY 2025 Plans:
Continue development, integration, and deployment of enterprise SatOps C2 services, such as flight dynamics and associated
standards and interfaces for the Research and Development Space and Missile Operations program (RDSMO) and protect and
defend mission partners. Continue deployment of cybersecurity, cryptography, and security architectures to support protect
and defend capabilities. Continue integration and testing with mission-partner developed unique software to meet end-to-end
C2 requirements. Continue growing infrastructure and network connectivity to support mission partners. Continue maturing a
commercial cloud architecture in support of protect and defend missions. Continue development of antenna networking services to

