 would be in addition to the civilian pay expenses budgeted in program elements 1206392SF and 1206398SF.$$, $$The Assistant Secretary of the Air Force for Space Acquisition and Integration directed the formation of a Combined Program Office (CPO) by merging Enterprise
Ground Services (EGS) from Space Systems Command (SSC) and Ground Command, Control, and Communications (GC3) from the Space Rapid Capabilities Office
(Space RCO). The CPO is called the Rapid Resilient Command and Control (R2C2) CPO and utilizes the Space RCO acquisition authorities under the Space RCO
Program Executive Officer to execute funding in the EGS and GC3 program elements to develop an extensible, scalable, modular ground segment solution capable of
supporting protect and defend missions of the United States Space Force. Combined EGS and GC3 funding will be used wholly and directly to support CPO activities.
R2C2 will continue development and integration of the satellite operations ground segment solution (SatOps) to support the protect and defend mission set, including,
but not limited to, capabilities and services needed to perform mission control.

 This program element may include necessary civilian pay expenses required to manage, execute, and deliver weapon system capability. The use of such program funds
 would be in addition to the civilian pay expenses budgeted in program elements 1206392SF and 1206398SF.

B. Accomplishments/Planned Programs ($ in Millions)                                                                                  FY 2024         FY 2025     FY 2026
Title: Rapid Resilient Command and Control (R2C2) Satellite Command and Control Services                                                    -            0.000      56.270
Description: Develop and integrate common satellite operations ground segment solution (SatOps) command and control
(C2) services in cloud environments. Refine standards and interfaces, develop, and implement cybersecurity and cryptography
requirements, develop training, address Zero Trust, mature antenna network services and connectivity, and integrate capabilities
into the enterprise. Support mission partner demonstrations, integration, and test of mission-unique software.

FY 2025 Plans:
N/A
FY 2026 Plans:

B. Accomplishments/Planned Programs ($ in Millions)                                                                                    FY 2024   FY 2025       FY 2026
Will continue development, integration, and deployment of enterprise SatOps C2 services for protect and defend missions,
including science and technology, prototype, and operational mission partners in advancement of protect and defend activities.
Will continue deployment of cybersecurity, cryptography, and security architectures to support protect and defend capabilities.
Will continue integration and testing with mission-partner developed unique software to meet end-to-end satellite mission control
requirements. Will continue growing infrastructure, network, and data system connectivity to support mission partners to improve
resiliency, to include ground entry points and enabling operational C2 in support of satellite C2 for protect and defend activities.
Will continue maturing cloud architecture in support of protect and defend missions. Will continue development of antenna
networking services and test assets to enable mission planning and scheduling for commercial and government antennas.
Will continue risk reduction demos as test assets become available. Will begin developing, integrating, testing, and evaluating
automation technologies to enhance mission control and engineering management capabilities for protect and defend missions.
Will support external agencies with test and checkout (TACO) space vehicles to facilitate test and checkout activities to ensure
software quality and performance in support of protect and defend missions.
FY 2025 to FY 2026 Increase/Decrease Statement:
FY 2026 Satellite Command and Control Services funding increased by 56.270 million due to transfer from PE 1206770SF,
Enterprise Ground Services. This includes a reduction for Advisory and Assistance Services efficiencies. FY25 funding was in PE
1206857SF, Space Rapid Capabilities Office due to a congressionally directed transfer.
Title: Rapid Resilient Command and Control (R2C2) Cloud Infrastructure and Platform/Antenna Services                                         -       0.000         49.950
Description: Maintain hardware and software baselines, update software licenses, integrate cybersecurity, and provide helpdesk
operations with associated training, to include support for developing software for cloud-hosted and antenna scheduling and
command and control (C2).

FY 2025 Plans:
N/A
FY 2026 Plans:
Will continue support activities and facilities for enterprise satellite operations ground segment solution (SatOps) C2 services
for protect and defend mission partners, including science and technology, prototype, and operational mission partners. Will
continue using R2C2 SatOps ground segment services and antenna networking services, to include maintaining software
baselines, expanding and supporting cloud environments, updating software licenses, facilitating user engagements, continuing
24x7 help desk operations, associated training, and cybersecurity support. Will continue service center capabilities to support
mission partners developing, integrating, testing, and operating R2C2 SatOps services. Will accomplish necessary infrastructure

