Description: Commercial Capabilities Integration & Transition

FY 2026 Plans:
Commercial Capabilities Integration & Transition: Performs Commercial Technology Research & Development Adaptation and
Acceleration into Air Force Nuclear Enterprise and Air Force Global Strike Command Mission Areas.
FY 2027 Plans:
Commercial Capabilities Integration & Transition: Performs Commercial Technology Research & Development Adaptation and
Acceleration into Air Force Nuclear Enterprise and Air Force Global Strike Command Mission Areas.
FY 2026 to FY 2027 Increase/Decrease Statement:
2026 to 2027 increase due to inflation.
                                                                               Accomplishments/Planned Programs Subtotals                     -        1.082          1.105

                                                                                                                   FY 2025    FY 2026
Congressional Add: B-52 Agile Pod                                                                                        -      15.000
FY 2026 Plans: Build on the 2025 AFRL contract to enhance the FORGE prototype currently being developed
by adding insertion of Artificial Intelligence/Machine Learning capabilities, new hardware sets, an improved
operating system, software/hardware integration lab testing, final developmental flight testing, validation and
verification, and initial aircraft integration.
Congressional Add: B-52 Modernization and Sustainment Technologies Development                                            -      29.700
FY 2026 Plans: Continue to execute innovative projects aimed at integrating the best commercial capabilities
into the Air Force Global Strike Command mission set as well as access the best and most innovative
technologies with a key focus on Beyond line-of-sight communications, data integration and processing, and
directed energy technologies.
Congressional Add: Assessment for Future Investments                                                                      -      29.000
FY 2026 Plans: Continue to identify mission needs and allow commercial companies an opportunity show their
technologies for future development. Funding will be used to demonstrate/prototype commercial technology in
military use cases to advance useability in the operational environment. Focus areas will be directed energy
prototyping, quantum sensing, tactical network experimentation, and reusable flight test vehicles.
Congressional Add: Advanced Fuels Development                                                                             -      10.000

                                                                                                                       FY 2025    FY 2026
FY 2026 Plans: Further testing and integration of the synthetic endothermic fuel developed for B-52 altitude
enhancement into high-speed applications. Testing freeze-point, viscosity, thrust, and emissions within
appropriate small-scale engines to characterize performance expectations relevant to B-52 Operations.
Congressional Add: Bomber Generation Tracking Automation Software                                                             -       5.000
FY 2026 Plans: Complete development and field the B-52 automated bomber generation tracking tool,
LineSync, within a Cloud One Impact-Level 6 environment.
Congressional Add: Legacy Weapon System Software Modernization                                                                -       5.000
FY 2026 Plans: Work to complete development and field the B-52 automated bomber generation tracking tool,
LineSync, within a Cloud One Impact-Level 6 environment by modernizing the historically manual and outdated
process of using checklists, handwritten data entry, and radio calls, by centralizing and incorporating data into a
near-real time (NRT) situational awareness tool.
