C. Accomplishments/Planned Programs ($ in Millions)                                                                                   FY 2025       FY 2026       FY 2027
Title: ATS Modernization and Digital Transformation                                                                                       4.699        11.942         1.200
Description: In an effort to develop and modernize ATS that maximize warfighter core capabilities across spectrum of DoW
weapon systems; accelerates technology development and transition of game-changing technologies into new and existing ATS,
the Automatic Test System has created the ATS Modernization/Digital Transformation Cell.

C. Accomplishments/Planned Programs ($ in Millions)                                                                                   FY 2025    FY 2026        FY 2027

Joint Force/All MAJCOMs depend on ATS digital transformation leveraging Model-Based Systems Engineering (MBSE), Agile SW
development, and Open Systems Architecture

Digital Transformation and Innovation are vital.
The Challenge: A next-gen avionics system needs a test program, a process that traditionally takes years of manual effort.
The Old Way: Engineers would write thousands of pages of technical specifications, leading to translation errors and massive
delays.
The Digital Shift: The system is now designed entirely within a Model-Based Systems Engineering (MBSE) environment.
The Digital Twin: This digital model becomes the "single source of truth" for all design, manufacturing, and sustainment data.
Automated Generation: The test program and all requirements are now automatically generated directly from the digital model.
The Result: The test solution is developed in parallel with the hardware, cutting the delivery schedule from years down to months.
Continuous Evolution: When the system's software is updated, the digital model instantly regenerates a new, fully compliant test
program.
The Strategic Win: This digital ecosystem accelerates capability delivery to the warfighter and ensures testers evolve at the speed
of software.

FY 2026 Plans:
Provides funding for engineering and manufacturing development and modernization of ATS/equipment for all USAF major
weapon systems. Includes common (used on more than one weapon system) and peculiar (unique to one weapon system),
which directly support aircraft maintenance requirements. This IPT has been tasked with risk reduction of ATS by improving
modernization and digital material management to enhance and secure the future of ATS. Projects have been established to
secure the future and security of automatic test systems.
The Foundational Enabler for the Future Fight: This program is the only path to fielding the test solutions required for the Air
Force's next-generation platforms (NGAD, B-21, Sentinel) and the core strategic goal of achieving 'operational flexibility and
agility.' It is not an upgrade; it is a prerequisite for the future force.
The Game-Changing Solution: It delivers this capability by executing the AF Digital Strategy—using Model-Based Systems
Engineering (MBSE), Digital Twins, and MOSA to slash development timelines from years to months. This ensures our test
solutions evolve at the speed of software, keeping pace with agile adversaries.
FY 2027 Plans:
Identify, research, and facilitate innovative solutions for current and future ATS products, challenges, and needs. Implement
digital technology to modernize and improve ATS operations, products and services that transform system management into
digital formats.

C. Accomplishments/Planned Programs ($ in Millions)                                                                                  FY 2025    FY 2026        FY 2027

Efforts include ruggedized cables for B-52 Multi-User Systems Tester Armament Next Generation (MUSTANG), CACI - Modeling,
on ramp fees associated with the award of ATS's 10-year $980M Multiple Award Indefinite Delivery-Indefinite Quantity (IDIQ),
ATSA I, which is a mandatory source contracts providing a rapid award approach for the procurement, development, and
sustainment of the goods and services, supporting life-cycle of legacy items and future requirements for the program office.

Innovation - Modernizing of historical standards and processes by introducing new methods, ideas, services, technologies, or
products.
Digital Transformation - Integration of digital technology into all areas of the business, fundamentally changing how ATS operates
and delivers value to customers.
